18
00:00:12,150 --> 00:00:15,150
http://hiqve.com/

19
00:00:18,439 --> 00:00:21,025
<i>A government toppled by civil war.</i>

20
00:00:21,359 --> 00:00:24,779
<i>Refusing to accept Prince Lee-Char
as the next ruler of Mon Cala,</i>

21
00:00:24,987 --> 00:00:27,573
<i>the Quarren people
join the Separatist alliance,</i>

22
00:00:27,782 --> 00:00:30,535
<i>and launch an all-out attack
on the Mon Calamari.</i>

23
00:00:31,077 --> 00:00:32,286
<i>Caught unprepared,</i>

24
00:00:32,370 --> 00:00:36,082
<i>the young prince and his Jedi protectors
are quickly overwhelmed</i>

25
00:00:36,123 --> 00:00:39,752
<i>and forced to retreat into caves
far below the capital city,</i>

26
00:00:40,002 --> 00:00:44,090
<i>leaving Count Dooku and his allies
to plan their next move.</i>

27
00:00:44,882 --> 00:00:48,177
<i>And the young prince,
has he been captured?</i>

28
00:00:48,261 --> 00:00:49,428
No, My Lord.

29
00:00:49,470 --> 00:00:51,597
Unfortunately he escaped capture,

30
00:00:51,639 --> 00:00:55,142
and is hiding with what's left of the Jedi
and their army.

31
00:00:55,476 --> 00:00:58,729
<i>Do not underestimate this boy, Tamson.</i>

32
00:00:58,813 --> 00:01:00,815
<i>He must not become a symbol</i>

33
00:01:00,856 --> 00:01:04,026
<i>for the Mon Calamari people to rally behind.</i>

34
00:01:04,110 --> 00:01:07,446
This child is but a coward. He is no leader.

35
00:01:07,697 --> 00:01:09,407
<i>That is irrelevant.</i>

36
00:01:09,490 --> 00:01:12,994
<i>The whispering of his name
can rekindle hope,</i>

37
00:01:13,452 --> 00:01:17,915
<i>and hope is something
we cannot allow our enemy to possess.</i>

38
00:01:17,999 --> 00:01:21,711
Excuse me, Count Dooku,
but what of the prisoners?

39
00:01:21,961 --> 00:01:23,254
<i>They are to be processed.</i>

40
00:01:23,671 --> 00:01:26,382
<i>Internment camps
have been set up below the city.</i>

41
00:01:26,465 --> 00:01:27,842
<i>Gather the rabble there.</i>

42
00:01:28,134 --> 00:01:29,719
<i>Then set them to work.</i>

43
00:01:30,011 --> 00:01:33,848
Surely, you do not mean all of them.
The women and children...

44
00:01:34,015 --> 00:01:36,017
<i>Are to be sent as well.</i>

45
00:01:36,100 --> 00:01:37,226
<i>Is that understood?</i>

46
00:01:37,685 --> 00:01:39,312
Yes, My Lord.

47
00:01:39,478 --> 00:01:42,607
<i>Tamson, I'm sending you reinforcements.</i>

48
00:01:42,690 --> 00:01:46,527
<i>Hold them in reserve
and wait for the Republic's next move.</i>

49
00:01:46,611 --> 00:01:48,571
As you wish, Count Dooku.

50
00:01:54,910 --> 00:01:58,539
We've lost contact with all
clone troopers and Mon Cala soldiers.

51
00:01:58,706 --> 00:02:00,249
The Quarren ambushed us.

52
00:02:00,374 --> 00:02:03,669
They were ready to attack
long before the peace talks came to an end.

53
00:02:03,878 --> 00:02:05,755
<i>Desperate, the situation is.</i>

54
00:02:05,921 --> 00:02:08,382
<i>Reinforce your position, clones, we can...</i>

55
00:02:08,633 --> 00:02:11,844
Master, please repeat.
Are you sending reinforcements?

56
00:02:12,219 --> 00:02:13,387
<i>You're breaking up.</i>

57
00:02:15,723 --> 00:02:16,932
Are they coming?

58
00:02:17,141 --> 00:02:18,643
I don't know.

59
00:02:18,726 --> 00:02:22,563
But they know our situation.
They must know to send help.

60
00:02:22,605 --> 00:02:24,732
Yeah, but it may take them a while
to get here.

61
00:02:24,815 --> 00:02:27,568
We're gonna have to get ourselves
to the surface and get off this rock.

62
00:02:27,818 --> 00:02:29,737
I will not leave my people to die.

63
00:02:30,071 --> 00:02:35,117
With all due respect, Your Highness,
if we stay, we all die.

64
00:02:36,661 --> 00:02:39,705
We must reach the surface
and see if our ship is still there.

65
00:02:39,747 --> 00:02:42,124
The prince will decide our course of action.

66
00:02:42,458 --> 00:02:45,419
I think it is best for us
to try and escape using your ship.

67
00:02:45,795 --> 00:02:47,797
As you wish, Your Highness. Follow me.

68
00:02:58,766 --> 00:03:00,935
It'll take us days
to outfit another clone regiment

69
00:03:01,018 --> 00:03:02,019
for underwater combat.

70
00:03:02,436 --> 00:03:04,647
<i>Days our friends do not have.</i>

71
00:03:04,730 --> 00:03:09,026
Perhaps we should look to armies
other than clones to help our cause.

72
00:03:09,235 --> 00:03:11,112
What do you suggest?

73
00:03:11,779 --> 00:03:15,157
A suitable ally, we must find,
to help with this mission.

74
00:03:15,366 --> 00:03:19,620
<i>Yes, an underwater race
that has a standing army,</i>

75
00:03:19,704 --> 00:03:22,123
<i>and is close enough to send help quickly.</i>

76
00:03:24,041 --> 00:03:25,584
<i>Naboo?</i>

77
00:03:25,793 --> 00:03:28,754
Yes, to the Gungans, we must look.

78
00:03:28,838 --> 00:03:30,464
We shall contact them immediately.

79
00:03:45,938 --> 00:03:48,649
That's a lot of enemy troops
between us and the surface.

80
00:03:48,691 --> 00:03:51,527
It's no problem.
I just hope you're a fast swimmer.

81
00:03:51,819 --> 00:03:54,155
Says the boy from the desert planet.

82
00:03:54,238 --> 00:03:56,699
Are you certain your ship is still there?

83
00:03:57,158 --> 00:03:58,492
There's only one way to find out.

84
00:03:58,951 --> 00:04:01,829
I'll create a diversion
so you can get past those patrols.

85
00:04:02,163 --> 00:04:04,206
All right. Try to get a mini-sub or two.

86
00:04:04,623 --> 00:04:06,000
It'll help us speed to the surface.

87
00:04:06,459 --> 00:04:07,793
No problem.

88
00:04:48,918 --> 00:04:50,503
Ahsoka, you're up first.

89
00:04:50,544 --> 00:04:52,379
Take the prince and Senator Tills.

90
00:04:52,421 --> 00:04:53,881
Got it!

91
00:05:17,404 --> 00:05:20,699
<i>Sir, the Jedi have reappeared
with the prince.</i>

92
00:05:23,536 --> 00:05:25,579
<i>They are headed to the surface.</i>

93
00:05:25,663 --> 00:05:26,664
Predictable.

94
00:05:27,456 --> 00:05:29,750
Let them get within sight of their ship.

95
00:05:30,167 --> 00:05:35,130
I want them to watch their hope
sink to the bottom of the sea.

96
00:05:37,424 --> 00:05:38,425
There's the ship.

97
00:05:38,592 --> 00:05:39,635
Still in one piece.

98
00:05:46,892 --> 00:05:47,977
Spring the trap.

99
00:06:04,410 --> 00:06:05,661
Oh!

100
00:06:13,794 --> 00:06:16,422
Well, Prince,
how do you feel about fighting again?

101
00:06:16,630 --> 00:06:18,632
Master Jedi, we're too vulnerable here.

102
00:06:18,716 --> 00:06:20,467
We must reach the sea floor.

103
00:06:20,759 --> 00:06:23,637
Grab onto the debris.
Let it carry you to the bottom.

104
00:06:25,723 --> 00:06:27,349
I think I'm getting seasick.

105
00:06:59,423 --> 00:07:03,093
-Back so soon?
-Yeah, the ship had some problems.

106
00:07:03,177 --> 00:07:05,346
I can see that, all around me.

107
00:07:05,512 --> 00:07:06,889
This is our only chance.

108
00:07:07,097 --> 00:07:09,767
We need to split up
and hide the prince's whereabouts.

109
00:07:10,017 --> 00:07:13,062
- I'm not sure that's the best strategy.
- I'm sure.

110
00:07:13,854 --> 00:07:15,981
Captain Ackbar's words are my own.

111
00:07:16,023 --> 00:07:18,525
It will give us the best chances of surviving
if we split up.

112
00:07:18,859 --> 00:07:20,027
As you wish.

113
00:07:20,069 --> 00:07:22,905
Ahsoka, you and the prince
go with Kit and take the clones.

114
00:07:22,988 --> 00:07:24,782
I'll take the senators and Captain Ackbar.

115
00:07:24,907 --> 00:07:25,908
Lay low.

116
00:07:26,367 --> 00:07:28,994
Our only hope is that Master Yoda
can send help in time.

117
00:07:29,370 --> 00:07:32,498
No, Prince Lee-Char is our only hope.

118
00:08:12,621 --> 00:08:14,581
Master Yoda, sir,

119
00:08:14,707 --> 00:08:17,418
to what's we owing
the pleasure of your transmission?

120
00:08:17,710 --> 00:08:19,753
<i>Your help, the Republic needs.</i>

121
00:08:20,045 --> 00:08:23,590
Something's telling me
it's big help you need. No?

122
00:08:23,924 --> 00:08:26,427
<i>Senator Amidala, your long-time ally,</i>

123
00:08:26,927 --> 00:08:29,138
<i>trapped on an occupied planet, she is.</i>

124
00:08:29,763 --> 00:08:30,848
Hmm.

125
00:08:31,557 --> 00:08:35,144
Mesa needs some thinking time
to respond to this a news.

126
00:08:35,394 --> 00:08:37,438
Thinking ! Nosa thinking.

127
00:08:37,730 --> 00:08:41,900
Mesa thinking Padmé would help us,
has helped us, big time.

128
00:08:42,109 --> 00:08:44,194
Wesa gots to help her now.

129
00:08:44,278 --> 00:08:46,989
Yo us a right. Thinking time's done.

130
00:08:47,156 --> 00:08:48,949
Wesa need to be leaving now.

131
00:09:04,965 --> 00:09:09,136
I don't think we've been followed.
Commander Monnk, post a lookout.

132
00:09:10,429 --> 00:09:13,515
We have no army and we don't know
if reinforcements are coming.

133
00:09:13,599 --> 00:09:15,184
What are our options?

134
00:09:15,267 --> 00:09:18,270
We sit tight. There's not much we can do.

135
00:09:28,989 --> 00:09:30,532
Sir, you better come see this.

136
00:09:45,839 --> 00:09:48,509
So many prisoners!
Where are they taking them?

137
00:09:48,592 --> 00:09:50,302
To become slaves.

138
00:09:50,344 --> 00:09:52,971
I can't believe Nossor Ri and the Quarren
agreed to this.

139
00:09:53,222 --> 00:09:56,725
Count Dooku rules here for now,
not the Quarren.

140
00:09:57,017 --> 00:10:01,021
What you see, Prince,
is the future of all the people on this world,

141
00:10:01,105 --> 00:10:03,023
Mon Cala and Quarren,

142
00:10:03,107 --> 00:10:05,192
all slaves for Count Dooku.

143
00:10:23,127 --> 00:10:26,922
Captain Ackbar, which of these structures
houses the city's interplanetary scanners?

144
00:10:27,422 --> 00:10:30,884
It's over there, across the square. Why?

145
00:10:30,968 --> 00:10:34,555
Well, just in case
Master Yoda is sending reinforcements,

146
00:10:34,596 --> 00:10:37,141
I thought it would be helpful if the enemy
couldn't tell they were coming.

147
00:10:37,391 --> 00:10:38,976
If we knock out those sensors,

148
00:10:39,059 --> 00:10:42,563
they won't see our reinforcements
until they're right on top of the city.

149
00:10:42,604 --> 00:10:44,565
Assuming someone is coming.

150
00:10:44,648 --> 00:10:47,901
I am sure
Master Yoda will find a way to send help.

151
00:10:47,943 --> 00:10:50,028
Anakin, it's your move.

152
00:10:50,070 --> 00:10:51,446
Follow me.

153
00:11:04,501 --> 00:11:06,753
There must be something more I can do.

154
00:11:06,837 --> 00:11:09,548
I know it's hard, but you have to be patient.

155
00:11:10,340 --> 00:11:13,594
But you saw my people. I failed them.

156
00:11:14,094 --> 00:11:19,433
No, remember Captain Ackbar's words,
"You are the hope of your people."

157
00:11:19,725 --> 00:11:22,144
As long as you live, they will endure.

158
00:11:22,728 --> 00:11:25,564
I need an army. We have to fight back.

159
00:11:25,898 --> 00:11:29,193
You don't have to carry a sword
to be powerful.

160
00:11:29,276 --> 00:11:32,738
Some leaders' strength
is inspiring greatness in others.

161
00:11:33,280 --> 00:11:35,199
But my people don't even know I'm alive.

162
00:11:35,282 --> 00:11:38,285
How can I inspire them
if they think I'm dead?

163
00:11:50,255 --> 00:11:53,425
Okay, just cover me.
I'm gonna have to concentrate.

164
00:11:53,717 --> 00:11:55,969
Concentrate? Concentrate on what?

165
00:11:56,261 --> 00:11:58,138
Bringing that building down.

166
00:12:09,983 --> 00:12:11,026
Anakin, hurry.

167
00:12:43,225 --> 00:12:44,309
What's happening? Report!

168
00:12:44,685 --> 00:12:47,896
We've lost all radar and sonar scanning, sir.

169
00:12:48,063 --> 00:12:51,608
-Reestablish the connections.
-We cannot, sir.

170
00:12:51,692 --> 00:12:52,693
Why not?

171
00:12:52,943 --> 00:12:56,071
The building that housed the radar is gone.

172
00:12:58,699 --> 00:12:59,992
We're blind.

173
00:13:00,033 --> 00:13:01,285
Prepare for an attack.

174
00:13:01,368 --> 00:13:04,496
But there was nothing on the scope
prior to the attack.

175
00:13:04,621 --> 00:13:08,292
That is precisely why we must assume
an attack is imminent!

176
00:13:08,667 --> 00:13:10,168
Guards, to me!

177
00:13:11,712 --> 00:13:13,297
Where are you going?

178
00:13:13,463 --> 00:13:17,551
To find that meddling prince
and his Jedi friends!

179
00:13:41,450 --> 00:13:44,161
At least we're taking attention away
from the prince.

180
00:14:01,845 --> 00:14:03,972
Oh, no, the prince... Hurry!

181
00:14:08,435 --> 00:14:10,562
The prince, he's alive!

182
00:14:10,604 --> 00:14:11,605
Look there!

183
00:14:11,938 --> 00:14:13,940
People of Mon Cala,

184
00:14:14,024 --> 00:14:17,569
all people of Mon Cala
who would not be slaves,

185
00:14:17,611 --> 00:14:18,612
have hope.

186
00:14:18,779 --> 00:14:20,739
We will fight for you, Prince.

187
00:14:20,947 --> 00:14:23,658
You will not be prisoners much longer.

188
00:14:23,742 --> 00:14:25,827
Okay, I think the show is over.

189
00:14:25,911 --> 00:14:28,038
The guards will be coming. We have to go.

190
00:14:48,100 --> 00:14:49,810
Wesa ready.

191
00:15:15,043 --> 00:15:18,463
Gungans. The tide has turned in our favor.

192
00:15:18,505 --> 00:15:21,591
Let's free my people. Attack!

193
00:15:52,873 --> 00:15:56,001
Ani, mesa so happy to see you.

194
00:15:56,209 --> 00:15:57,711
Perfect timing, Jar Jar.

195
00:15:58,044 --> 00:16:03,133
Whats a? Mesa can't hear so good
since me submerged.

196
00:16:40,504 --> 00:16:43,548
Tamson. Tamson, come in. Where are you?

197
00:16:44,216 --> 00:16:47,135
The Republic reinforcements
are overwhelming our defenses.

198
00:16:47,677 --> 00:16:50,597
We must retreat. We must retreat now.

199
00:16:50,805 --> 00:16:52,807
<i>I warned you this attack was coming.</i>

200
00:16:52,891 --> 00:16:55,268
<i>Where are the Jedi
concentrating their attack?</i>

201
00:16:55,769 --> 00:16:57,812
There are two groups of Jedi,

202
00:16:57,896 --> 00:16:59,689
one, in the lower city center,

203
00:16:59,773 --> 00:17:03,026
and two, releasing the prisoners
near the coral base.

204
00:17:03,318 --> 00:17:06,571
<i>The prisoners!
The prince must be with them.</i>

205
00:17:06,613 --> 00:17:10,450
<i>I'm committing the reinforcements
that Count Dooku sent to the attack.</i>

206
00:17:10,534 --> 00:17:12,577
<i>He will not escape this time.</i>

207
00:17:18,583 --> 00:17:19,584
Churn them up.

208
00:17:53,243 --> 00:17:56,037
Stay in the center, there's less turbulence.

209
00:19:09,694 --> 00:19:10,695
Anakin!

210
00:19:14,949 --> 00:19:17,369
Skywalker, we've got one chance.

211
00:19:44,020 --> 00:19:46,898
Ahsoka, escape with the prince.
I'll hold him off.

212
00:19:59,786 --> 00:20:01,454
Sever one of the legs.

213
00:21:06,770 --> 00:21:08,396
Find the prince!

214
00:21:08,480 --> 00:21:09,606
Find him!

215
00:21:14,861 --> 00:21:17,697
Now you and I are the only ones left.

216
00:21:18,198 --> 00:21:20,033
I'm sorry, Lee-Char.

217
00:21:20,116 --> 00:21:23,536
I know what I must do.
I know my people need me.

218
00:21:24,037 --> 00:21:26,206
I just don't know how to win this war.

219
00:21:26,706 --> 00:21:31,544
Look, I know you're scared,
but you can't let your fear control you.

220
00:21:31,753 --> 00:21:33,129
Aren't you scared?

221
00:21:33,588 --> 00:21:35,924
I used to be, all the time,

222
00:21:36,007 --> 00:21:39,469
until I realized that
if you make decisions out of fear,

223
00:21:39,552 --> 00:21:41,679
you're more likely to be wrong.

224
00:21:41,721 --> 00:21:45,016
I will unify Mon Cala again, I promise.

225
00:21:46,267 --> 00:21:47,769
We have to go.

226
00:21:47,793 --> 00:21:52,793
http://hiqve.com/

